INSERT INTO wp_postmeta VALUES("621","157","section_1","<div class=\"col-sm-12 col-md-12\">\r\n<h2 class=\"heading\">Exchange 2003 to 2007/2010 Migration</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"ccol-sm-12 col-md-6\">\r\n<h3 class=\"lead\">Out with the old, now onto something very new.</h3>\r\nThe introduction of the CAS/HUB architecture allows for sophisticated Enterprise level features to be rolled out in your organization, but not without cost. For companies that maintain small to medium Exchange 2003 environments where often just a single server manages their mail, deciding how many servers to run and what roles to make each server responsible for is often a complex task.\r\n\r\nFirewall and internal routing considerations can make the new OWA and OMA handling wonderfully flexible - if configured optimally. If not, it can turn into a bandwidth burden on your network that provides external e-mail access at a penalty to those inside your organization.\r\n\r\nSarbanes-Oxley (SOX) and HIPPA compliant journaling and backup features are now much more accessible than in previous versions, but if configured without a long-term outlook can cause your mail store to balloon over time. Users can see delays in their day-to-day usage that worsen over time, just so that IT can keep copies of old messages that they often don\'t care about.\r\n\r\nNew account migration options allow much greater flexibilty rolling out the new version. Take the company offline and upgrade the entire organization at once? Migrate particular users/departments sequentially allowing for minimal downtime and rollback options?\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-sm-12 col-md-6\">\r\n<h3 class=\"lead\">A variety of support options to meet your needs:</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li class=\"well\">\r\n<h4>Hands off migration.</h4>\r\nWe work with you to determine the migration path best suited for your organizational structure and then take care of everything from there. Once the migration has been completed, we bring you up to speed on the changes during a brief training session highlighting the administration differences between your new and previous versions of Exchange. A \"C\" level check box item accomplished, done quickly and without costly and time consuming training for your internal staff.</li>\r\n	<li class=\"well\">\r\n<h4>Sequential account migration.</h4>\r\nYou approve a group of users to migrate and then go home. Our staff of experienced technicians remotely migrate the users after hours and monitors the process. We report any issues to you during the migration and prepare the accounts for use by the staff when they arrive the next morning. Painless support, with the migration progressing at your own pace.</li>\r\n	<li class=\"well\">\r\n<h4>Kick-start migration.</h4>\r\nSimilar to the sequential migration where NovaStar helps to establish the new environment. We migrate the first batch of users and confirm correct settings and all desired features are operational. Your staff is then trained on the migration process and proceeds with the remaining mailboxes on their own, contacting NovaStar as needed should any problems arise. Shortened learning curve, extended support only if you need it to keep costs low.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>");
