INSERT INTO wp_postmeta VALUES("644","159","section_3","<div class=\"row-fluid\">\r\n<div class=\"span12\">\r\n<div class=\"accordion-container\">\r\n<div class=\"row-fluid\">\r\n\r\nIn the old days it was called \"disaster recovery\". The business world demands a much more dynamic approach to securing the Enterprise. Power will go out. ISPs will disrupt and/or discontinue service. Some times these events will last only minutes or hours - so the solutions must be flexible enough to kick in quickly (no day long tape restores) but also able to relinquish control when normalcy is restored (no list of manual changes to the corporate firewall to shift traffic back).\r\n<h3>Mail routing that allows continuity during several types of outages</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"pointer\">\r\n	<li>What is the main purpose of e-mail during an event? Who are the highest priority client set that needs to be addressed?</li>\r\n	<li>What is more important, missing inbound messages or being able to continue sending outbound messages?</li>\r\n	<li>Filter messages yourself, to lower monthly costs? External filter, to isolate and secure your mail server from the public Internet?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Multi-point access to data</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"pointer\">\r\n	<li>Any architecture with a single point of data availability failure is ripe for a downtime disruption.</li>\r\n	<li>Even with DFS and other technologies in place if they are all reliant upon the same data store then the failure point has merely been shifted, not eliminated.</li>\r\n	<li>Based upon your business needs, compliance obligations, budget, revisioning constraints and timeline for a restore in the event of data loss the best solution for you might not be a single solution.</li>\r\n	<li>Replication of data between locations vs. off-site backup? Off-site to the public cloud, a controlled 3rd party cloud, your own cloud or standard machines co-located at another facility?</li>\r\n	<li>We can help you architect a plan that meets your needs and also allows you to retain as much, or as little, possession over the stored data as you like.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Network convergence</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"pointer\">\r\n	<li>Wireless devices bridging onto your wired infrstructure can cause hassles if they are not controlled. Are you limiting what impact they have on your network or just waiting for it to become a problem?</li>\r\n	<li>The cost of high speed networking equipment has decreased substantially in the past few years, do you have redundant links on standby for your backbones?</li>\r\n	<li>Spare/redundant hardware in place in the switching layer?</li>\r\n	<li>Do you know what, and who, is taking the largest share of your network traffic - really?</li>\r\n	<li>Our testing and evaluations services can help you determine fault tolerant hardware solutions that add stabilty and minimize downtime.</li>\r\n	<li>Our analysis services can analyze your network and warn you of potential problems and help you troubleshoot throughput and latency issues that you\'re experiencing.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"clearfix\"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>");
