INSERT INTO wp_postmeta VALUES("1489","204","section_7_heading","Methods of Recovery");
INSERT INTO wp_postmeta VALUES("1490","204","_section_7_heading","field_550c6bb48d4ed");
INSERT INTO wp_postmeta VALUES("1491","204","section_7","NovaStar purchases our customers’ used I.T. equipment at fair market wholesale value after testing and auditing. We also offer to sell the equipment on consignment where our customers share in the risk and can benefit from potentially higher resale values. NovaStar can manage employee purchase options and system redeployments too.\r\n\r\nThose customers choosing consignment have the ability to track their inventory. This includes an in-stock view, which reflects the real-time status of client inventory and an inbound history report, which is a historical view in to what equipment was received, when, and from where, all via our secure client portal.\r\n\r\nSustainability is at the core of what NovaStar Solutions does. Our main goal is to retrieve value wherever possible from equipment returned to our facility for remarketing. Over 95% of the equipment sent to us is resold on the secondary market. If a received system is deemed defective and not repairable, NovaStar will harvest the system for its working components, and the rest will be disposed of properly in accordance with local laws and regulations. Because NovaStar is an R2 Certified electronics waste recycler, every I.T. asset has an end point and you can rest assured your asset will not end up in landfill.\r\n\r\nNovaStar requires its downstream electronics waste partners to be R2 Certified and to use EPA approved standards and provide certificates of destruction. Annual audits are conducted of our downstream providers with NovaStar personnel inspecting our waste management partner’s facility.");
