INSERT INTO wp_posts VALUES("97","1","2015-02-13 18:54:25","2015-02-13 18:54:25","&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Increased core operating system security. Various aspects of the operating system have been modified to make it more difficult for applications to run without permission, as well as modifing files on the system without the users\' knowledge.</li>\r\n	<li>Network control over machine level detail via Group Policy Objects (GPO) has been vastly expanded. You can control more things, to a finer level of detail, than you could with either Windows XP or Windows Vista.</li>\r\n	<li>More complete and standard support for today\'s newer architecture machines. Multi-core and multi-socket machines are handled with a more advanced thread manager, allowing more performance to be achieved with existing hardware. Newer hardware takes this advantage even further with support for SSD/USB swap drives, virtualized component utilization and other features simply not available in Windows XP.</li>\r\n	<li>More direct and tightly integrated control with Windows Server 2008/2011 SBS/2012. If you have a Windows Server 2003 architecture, your Windows 7 clients will work without issue. But if you have any of the next generation Windows Server products you\'ll find additional control and configuration options available on the Windows 7/8 machines that can aid in creating a more standardized and more easily managed IT infrastructure. From deployment options to product update managment, administering Windows 7/8 boxes is just easier.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;","Why upgrade to Windows 7/8?","","trash","open","open","","why-is-it-worth-upgrading-to-windows-78","","","2015-03-31 19:43:56","2015-03-31 19:43:56","","0","http://novastar.dev/?p=97","0","post","","0");
