 account, in reality, it might not be the best choice.","4 Disadvantages of Seat Sharing for CAD/CAE","","inherit","open","open","","438-revision-v1","","","2015-04-01 13:12:02","2015-04-01 13:12:02","","438","http://novastar.dev/438-revision-v1/","0","revision","","0");
INSERT INTO wp_posts VALUES("440","1","2015-01-17 13:13:02","2015-01-17 13:13:02","Most discussion of innovations centers on the benefits of “disruptive technology.” For example Apple redefined the mobile phone industry with the iPhone and Dell’s build to order manufacturing model revolutionized the way we buy PC’s. For the most part, these innovations provide significant advantages and are generally viewed as positive developments.\r\n\r\nMany feel the same way about 3D printing, an emerging technology that has disrupted the mass production manufacturing industry. The new technology allows building products in units of one and has resulted in lower cost of small batch production, decreased time to market, and an increase in mass customization. Although these all are clearly benefits, the 3D boom also has raised concerns that need to be addressed. Here are three of them.\r\n\r\n<strong>Legal Issues</strong>\r\nAs more small companies and individuals acquire the capability to produce products, the question of liability for these products arises. For example, large manufacturers of helmets and toys are strictly regulated in the U. S. but these controls are difficult to extend to small one-off products.\r\n\r\nThere is also the issue of intellectual property protection. Designs and programs for creating 3D products can be copyrighted, but with a growing number of micro-manufacturers, the lines of ownership become blurred.\r\n\r\nFinally, with the low barrier to equipment acquisition, piracy problems are expected to grow. Making knockoffs of popular products becomes exponentially easier with 3D manufacturing.\r\n\r\n<strong>Security Issues</strong>\r\nUnfortunately there will always be those who will try to use new technologies for nefarious purposes. For example, in a time when the discussion over gun control has grown more contentious, 3D printing technology has added another debate point. Some people are using the technology to produce plastic firearms parts to make guns that can’t be discovered by metal detectors. Others are creating widgets that can fit into ATM’s allowing access to people’s bank accounts.\r\n\r\nAnother concern is that the advent of 3D technology enables a greater number of people and companies to get into the manufacturing business. This means a larger group of people now has access to proprietary corporate and government intellectual property. This increases the chances that this sensitive information could be made available for piracy or espionage.\r\n\r\n<strong>Environmental Impact</strong>\r\nWhile the flexibility of 3D technology enhances the ability to use standard materials and reduces excessive make ready in mass production runs making it more environmentally friendly, there are some downside risks to the environment.\r\n\r\nThe current 3D engines are energy hogs, sometimes using 50-100% more energy than conventional injection molding units. The evolving smaller manufacturers using this technology sometimes lack sufficient air quality controls making unhealthy emissions a concern. Finally, since producing small batches of products is so cost effective, it increases the chances of “design fatigue” which could increase disposals and add to the waste stream.\r\n\r\nA recent report from the Institute for National Strategic Studies addresses these issues and concludes that it’s “incumbent upon law enforcement and the legal profession to cooperate in protecting entrepreneurs; furthermore, the diplomatic community will need to work with foreign partners to protect American intellectual property abroad.”\r\n\r\nThough these concerns surrounding the growth of 3D printing need to be taken seriously, they should not be a reason to slow the development of the technology. Taken on balance, the benefits far outweigh the potential negatives. As with all new technologies, we need to be vigilant to ensure the growing 3D capability is being used for good rather than ill.","3 Concerns Surrounding 3D Printing","","publish","open","open","","3-concerns-surrounding-3d-printing","","","2015-04-13 14:36:44","2015-04-13 14:36:44","","0","http://novastar.dev/?p=440","0","post","","0");
