INSERT INTO wp_posts VALUES("446","1","2015-03-30 13:17:30","2015-03-30 13:17:30","Like organizations in most other industries, companies that rely on CAD technology face increasing pressure to reduce lead times, cut costs, and improve productivity. Balancing those needs while still maintaining a high level of quality is challenging. Advances in CAD processor technology, however, are proving to be a way for firms to meet that challenge.\r\n\r\nWorkstations built with traditional CPU technology gave way to stations employing GPU processing resulting in a significant uptick in performance. However, an even bigger boost in processing power has come with the use of high end Physics processing cards – more commonly known as Tesla cards for the brand name of the leader in the industry. The use of Tesla cards for visualization and simulation has dramatically changed the mid and high end workstation spaces and is revolutionizing the cluster space. These cards eliminate some of the lineal gains you get from faster processors and make these boxes produce far more analysis than previously possible. Prices have come down and drivers have gotten better, making these powerful tools more accessible to CAD operators in companies of all sizes.\r\n\r\n<strong>CPU vs. GPU vs. Tesla</strong>\r\nConventional CPU processing - a series of discrete actions performed sequentially one after the other – was limited and slow. To increase processing speeds, you had to purchase a new computer. The arrival of GPU cards - short for Graphics Processing Unit – took processing to another level. The accelerated computing from GPU provided parallel architecture consisting of thousands of smaller, more efficient cores designed to handle multiple tasks simultaneously. In a GPU workstation, resource intensive portions of an application are handled by the GPU leaving the rest of the app to run on the CPU. The result is fast, reliable rendering presented the way CAD users require. And if you needed more speed, you plugged in a new card every year or so.\r\n\r\nAs effective as GPU is, it pales next to the new generation of Tesla card processor technology. Tesla cards are designed to support specialized graphics engines that deliver the rasterizers and shaders required by professional CAD applications. They’ve taken the traditional GPU processor and added an ancillary chip set that specializes in the kind of high-end mathematics commonly used in the simulation CAD/CAM design FEA environments.\r\n\r\nThese high powered cards can rapidly handle advanced calculations like higher calculus, non destructive impact testing, linear analysis of a spline so you can do what-if scenarios like bending and flexing something to determine when it might snap, what it’s going to look like as it bends, and what structural properties it has at various bend points. Doing this with a GPU alone takes a long time, and doing it with a CPU augmented by a GPU takes even longer.\r\n\r\n<strong>Tesla Card Advantages</strong>\r\nAs an example, there could be a situation where you might have to wait an hour for a render or analysis but with a Tesla card it could be five minutes. Increased processing speeds provide engineers with several advantages. They are better able to meet deadlines that improve end user services levels. In organizations that share workstations among several users, faster processing means stations are likely to be more available improving efficiency. Productivity is also improved with the added throughput as organizations can take on more projects.\r\n\r\nThe added memory of Tesla cards are better able to handle the larger databases required for most projects engineers face. This increased computing power enables more and better analysis. Running Tesla cards allows engineers to test and compare multiple design concepts before going to prototype where with CPU they might only be able to test a single option. Users can also draw on larger data sets to develop more alternatives and more detailed solutions.\r\n\r\nThe growing adoption of Tesla cards promises to have a dramatic impact on the CAD world as users find more ways to leverage the advanced technology.","How Tesla Cards are Revolutionizing CAD Use","","publish","open","open","","how-tesla-cards-are-revolutionizing-cad-use","","","2015-04-13 14:36:32","2015-04-13 14:36:32","","0","http://novastar.dev/?p=446","0","post","","0");
