ed, you plugged in a new card every year or so.\r\n\r\nAs effective as GPU is, it pales next to the new generation of Tesla card processor technology. Tesla cards are designed to support specialized graphics engines that deliver the rasterizers and shaders required by professional CAD applications. They’ve taken the traditional GPU processor and added an ancillary chip set that specializes in the kind of high-end mathematics commonly used in the simulation CAD/CAM design FEA environments.\r\n\r\nThese high powered cards can rapidly handle advanced calculations like higher calculus, non destructive impact testing, linear analysis of a spline so you can do what-if scenarios like bending and flexing something to determine when it might snap, what it’s going to look like as it bends, and what structural properties it has at various bend points. Doing this with a GPU alone takes a long time, and doing it with a CPU augmented by a GPU takes even longer.\r\n\r\n<strong>Tesla Card Advantages</strong>\r\nAs an example, there could be a situation where you might have to wait an hour for a render or analysis but with a Tesla card it could be five minutes. Increased processing speeds provide engineers with several advantages. They are better able to meet deadlines that improve end user services levels. In organizations that share workstations among several users, faster processing means stations are likely to be more available improving efficiency. Productivity is also improved with the added throughput as organizations can take on more projects.\r\n\r\nThe added memory of Tesla cards are better able to handle the larger databases required for most projects engineers face. This increased computing power enables more and better analysis. Running Tesla cards allows engineers to test and compare multiple design concepts before going to prototype where with CPU they might only be able to test a single option. Users can also draw on larger data sets to develop more alternatives and more detailed solutions.\r\n\r\nThe growing adoption of Tesla cards promises to have a dramatic impact on the CAD world as users find more ways to leverage the advanced technology.","How Tesla Cards are Revolutionizing CAD Use","","inherit","open","open","","446-revision-v1","","","2015-04-01 13:17:30","2015-04-01 13:17:30","","446","http://novastar.dev/446-revision-v1/","0","revision","","0");
